<p>Meng To talked about his <a href="https://designcode.io/story" title="Meng To's personal story">personal story</a>. He dropped out college, to be a Web designer. Worked hard in the Valley to make it, only to be denied his Visa because he didnâ€™t have a college degree. With nothing to lose, he packed his things and went <a href="http://blog.mengto.com/traveling-designing/" title="Meng to travelling">traveling</a> around the world. To make ends meet he worked as a freelancer, and started writing Design+Code, his successful book teaching designers how to design with <a href="http://bohemiancoding.com/" title="Boheamian Coding">Sketch</a> and code with <a href="https://developer.apple.com/swift/" title="Swift">Swift</a>, to create quick prototypes of their ideas.</p>

<p>So far, Meng To has sold more than 13.000 copies of his book, helping out 6 young readers of his book to earn a scholarship for the <a href="https://developer.apple.com/wwdc/" title="WWDC">WWDC</a>, while making this year his first $1.000.000. An impressive storyâ€Šâ€”â€Što say the leastâ€Šâ€”â€Šthat wouldnâ€™t have been possible according Meng To without coding.</p>

